# ============================================================
# .GITIGNORE
# This file tells Git which files and folders to IGNORE —
# meaning they will NOT be uploaded to GitHub or shared.
#
# Why ignore these?
#   - __pycache__ and .pyc files are auto-generated by Python.
#     They are not part of your real code.
#   - model.pkl is a large binary file (can be 50MB+).
#     It should be regenerated locally, not stored in git.
#   - report.pdf is a generated output file. No need to track it.
#   - .env contains secret keys and passwords.
#     NEVER commit this file — it would expose your credentials.
# ============================================================

# Python auto-generated files — safe to delete, Python recreates them
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# The trained ML model — large binary, regenerate it by clicking "Train Model"
model.pkl

# Generated PDF report — recreate it by clicking "Generate PDF Report"
report.pdf

# Environment variables file — contains secrets like API keys, passwords
# NEVER commit this file to git
.env